# Cursor AI - Uiverse Component Instructions

## When User Says: "Add a Uiverse component"

### Step 1: Identify Component
Ask user for Uiverse.io URL or component description.

### Step 2: Create Template
1. Create `/templates/uiverse/[component-name].html`
2. Replace colors:
   - Any blue/purple/red → `#00e5ff` (cyan)
   - Any green → `#00ff88` (green)
   - Backgrounds → `#000` (black) or `rgba(0,0,0,0.6)`
3. Add cyan glow to white text:
   ```css
   text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0,229,255,0.6);
   ```
4. Change fonts to `'Poppins', sans-serif`
5. Use variables: `{{variable_name}}`

### Step 3: Add CSS
Add component styles to `/assets/css/uiverse-components.css`:
```css
/* ============================================
   [COMPONENT NAME] - Uiverse Adaptation
   ============================================ */

.component-name {
  /* Adapted styles here */
}
```

### Step 4: Register Defaults (Optional)
Add to `uiverse-loader.js` in `getDefaults()` function if component needs special defaults.

### Step 5: Show Usage Example
Provide this to user:
```javascript
UIverse.load('component-name', {
  property1: 'value1',
  property2: 'value2'
}, '#container-id');
```

## When User Says: "Add puppy cards to [page]"

### Quick Implementation:
```html
<!-- Add to HTML head -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/puppy-cards.css?v=20250128">

<!-- Add container where cards should appear -->
<div id="puppy-grid" class="uiverse-puppy-grid"></div>

<!-- Add before </body> -->
<script src="/assets/js/uiverse-loader.js"></script>
<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    fetch('/data/placeholder-puppies.json')
      .then(r => r.json())
      .then(d => UIverse.loadBulk('puppy-card', d, '#puppy-grid'));
  });
</script>
```

## When User Says: "Update puppy data"

Direct them to edit `/data/placeholder-puppies.json`:
```json
{
  "id": "puppy-x",
  "title": "Name",
  "subtitle": "Color • Gender",
  "price": "$X,XXX",
  "status": "Available",
  "image": "/assets/images/bulldogs/image.jpg",
  "link": "/page.html"
}
```

## When User Says: "Add [number] placeholder puppies"

Use this template and duplicate:
```json
{
  "id": "puppy-[n]",
  "title": "[Dog Name]",
  "subtitle": "[Color] • [Male/Female]",
  "price": "$7,500",
  "status": "Coming Soon",
  "image": "/assets/images/bulldogs/gallery/placeholder-[n].jpg",
  "link": "/available-puppies.html#puppy-[n]"
}
```

## When User Says: "Make it responsive"

Puppy cards are already responsive! Breakpoints:
- Desktop 1200px+: 4 columns
- Laptop 992-1199px: 3 columns
- Tablet 768-991px: 2 columns
- Mobile <768px: 1-2 columns

No additional work needed.

## When User Says: "Add loading state"

Already implemented! Default HTML in container:
```html
<div id="grid" class="uiverse-puppy-grid">
  <div style="grid-column: 1 / -1; text-align: center; padding: 60px 20px;">
    <div class="spinner-uiverse-large"></div>
    <p>Loading...</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

## When User Says: "Add error handling"

Wrap fetch in try-catch:
```javascript
try {
  const response = await fetch('/data/puppies.json');
  if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to load');
  const data = await response.json();
  await UIverse.loadBulk('puppy-card', data, '#grid');
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Error:', error);
  document.getElementById('grid').innerHTML = `
    <div style="text-align: center; padding: 60px 20px;">
      <p>Unable to load puppies. Please try again later.</p>
    </div>
  `;
}
```

## When User Says: "Filter by status"

```javascript
fetch('/data/puppies.json')
  .then(r => r.json())
  .then(data => {
    const filtered = data.filter(p => p.status === 'Available');
    UIverse.loadBulk('puppy-card', filtered, '#grid');
  });
```

## Available Components

1. **puppy-card** - Interactive puppy showcase
2. **glass-card** - Service/feature card
3. **hover-expand** - Expandable corner card
4. **btn-primary** - Primary CTA button (use class directly)
5. **btn-outline** - Outline CTA button (use class directly)

## Status Options

- `Available` - Green badge
- `Reserved` - Cyan badge
- `Coming Soon` - White badge
- `Sold` - Gray badge

## Color Palette (Always Use)

- Cyan: `#00e5ff`
- Green: `#00ff88`
- Black: `#000000`
- White: `#FFFFFF`
- Glow: `0 0 20px rgba(0,229,255,0.6)`

## Documentation Files

- `UIVERSE_QUICK_START.md` - Full guide
- `QUICK_COMMAND_REFERENCE.md` - Copy-paste commands
- `UIVERSE_SYSTEM_SUMMARY.md` - Implementation details
- `/templates/uiverse/README.md` - Technical docs

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ Don't create new components when existing ones work
❌ Don't use inline styles when CSS classes exist
❌ Don't forget to version CSS: `?v=YYYYMMDD`
❌ Don't skip error handling
❌ Don't load 100+ cards at once (paginate)
❌ Don't use colors outside brand palette

## Testing Checklist

Before marking complete:
- [ ] Test on mobile (375px viewport)
- [ ] Check hover states work
- [ ] Verify images load
- [ ] Test keyboard navigation
- [ ] Check console for errors
- [ ] Clear cache and test (Ctrl+Shift+R)

## Pro Tips

1. Always edit JSON, not HTML
2. Use existing classes when possible
3. Test on real mobile devices
4. Version assets for cache busting
5. Keep it simple - don't over-engineer

---

**When in doubt**, check `gallery.html` lines 502-1177 for working example.




